<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="1071" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="37.[585,818,855,879]" box="[585,818,855,879]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">
<heading box="[585,818,855,879]" centered="true" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071" reason="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[585,818,855,879]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vinculum" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[635,749,855,879]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Helcystogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trijunctum">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[635,749,855,879]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">trijunctum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[213,1170,926,1492]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">
This group is defined by the following characters: the ocellus absent, the antenna ciliate, the labial palpus with (
<figureCitation box="[528,645,958,982]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="9.[213,280,908,930]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,161,875]" captionTargetId="figure-5@9.[213,1170,161,875]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 4. Head of Helcystogramma spp. (A) Ocellus of H. perelegans (Omelko and Omelko); (B–D) labial palpus: (B) H. brevinodium sp. nov. holotype male; (C) H. rectangulum sp. nov. paratype male; (D) H. angustum sp. nov. paratype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5203577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5203577/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">Figure 4C</figureCitation>
) or without (
<figureCitation box="[797,916,958,982]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="9.[213,280,908,930]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,161,875]" captionTargetId="figure-5@9.[213,1170,161,875]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figure 4. Head of Helcystogramma spp. (A) Ocellus of H. perelegans (Omelko and Omelko); (B–D) labial palpus: (B) H. brevinodium sp. nov. holotype male; (C) H. rectangulum sp. nov. paratype male; (D) H. angustum sp. nov. paratype male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5203577" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5203577/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">Figure 4D</figureCitation>
) long scales on dorsal surface, the third segment shorter than second, the forewing usually with scale tufts at about middle and end of cell as well as at fold; the eighth tergite nearly straight anteriorly, the uncus narrowed from base to apex, its anterior margin concave triangularly, the gnathos blunt apically, the vinculum with distal part of lobes directed obliquely inward, usually thumb-shaped and blunt apically, the saccus broad, often bluntly rounded anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[439,568,1150,1174]" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="21.[213,280,753,775]" captionTargetBox="[213,1170,159,719]" captionTargetId="figure-5@21.[213,1170,159,720]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figure 16. Saccus of Helcystogramma spp. (A) H. lutatella (Herrich-Schäffer); (B) H. imagibicuneum sp. nov.; (C) H. perelegans (Omelko et Omelko); (D) H. flavilineolella Ponomarenko; (E) H. angustum sp. nov.; (F) saccal region of Dichomeris okadai (Moriuti)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5203605" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5203605/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">Figure 16E</figureCitation>
), the aedeagus nearly equal to or slightly shorter than valva, narrow and with clusters of spines distally in the male genitalia; the eighth tergite straight posteriorly, the antrum spined, the ductus bursae sclerotized distally, the corpus bursae densely spined on inner surface, usually protruding posteriorly on one side, and the ductus seminalis arising from apex of protrusion in the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="1071" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="37.[213,1170,926,1492]" pageId="37" pageNumber="1071">
